                  IMAGE CATEGORIZATION DEMONSTATION
                   Andrea Vedaldi  Andrew Zisserman
                     {vedaldi,az}@robots.ox.ac.uk

The package contains the following MATLAB functions:

standardizeImage.m -- rescale an image to a standard size
computeFeatures.m -- compute dense SIFT keypoints and descriptors
quantizeDescriptors.m -- quantize visual descriptors into visual words
computeHistogram.m -- compute a spatial histogram of visual words (starting from the features)
computeHistogramFromImage.m -- compute a histogram of visual words (starting from an image)
computeHistogramsFromImageList.m -- applies the above to a list of images
learnLinaerSVM.m -- learn a linear support vector machine

Demo scripts:

experiment1.m -- learn and test an image classifier

APPENDX (INSTALLATION)

Run MATLAB and execute the command PREPROCESS(). This will download
the VLFeat library (http://www.vlfeat.org) and the Caltech-4 image
collection. Then, it will compute a visual vocabulary and spatial
histograms of visual words for the Caltech-4 images.
